<subSubSection id="5A9465406E5B3F194044FD27FDC89477" pageId="15" pageNumber="104" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="123136CB6E5B3F194044FD27FDC89477" blockId="15.[270,1102,705,1100]" pageId="15" pageNumber="104">
<emphasis id="20FAEAD96E5B3F194044FD27FE019586" bold="true" box="[296,410,705,726]" pageId="15" pageNumber="104">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Elytra bright coppery green. Mentum with median tooth short and markedly bifid, length 
<emphasis id="20FAEAD96E5B3F19435DFD3AFDD895A2" bold="true" box="[561,579,732,754]" pageId="15" pageNumber="104">⅓</emphasis>
that of lateral lobe. Tarsomere 5 of posterior leg long and inserted into markedly emarginate tarsomere 4. Elytron with sutural apex minutely acuminate (5a).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
